            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": "The essay \"Southern Horrors: Lynch Law in All its Phases\" appeared in 1892 as a speech that Wells presented in New York City. It was printed in October of that year as a pamphlet (shown below). This piece argues forcefully against lynching logic, deconstructing the excuse that Black men raped white women. It delves deeply into the complications of sexuality and law in a time and place of profound social inequality."
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
